the international
race track of the Algarve.

15:15.515 --> 15:18.318
When we arrived,
mechanics from Porsche

15:18.318 --> 15:20.453
and McLaren pounced on
our cars,

15:20.453 --> 15:23.523
fettling them for
what was to come.

15:23.523 --> 15:26.593
And this meant Hammond and I
had some time to indulge

15:26.593 --> 15:30.597
in a spot
of childish point scoring.

15:30.597 --> 15:33.833
Which one of these is going
to be the fastest around
this track?

15:33.833 --> 15:35.235
- This?
- Yeah.

15:35.235 --> 15:37.537
Apart from this one,
which will be faster.

15:37.537 --> 15:40.173
It won't. Which one do you
think will be the fastest?

15:40.173 --> 15:42.109
- This one.
- This one.

15:42.109 --> 15:45.412
Porsche think the Porsche
will be fastest.
McLaren say the McLaren.

15:45.412 --> 15:47.547
How much is it
if I wanted to buy one?

15:47.547 --> 15:50.583
I think one was sold in
an auction for 1.8 million.

15:50.583 --> 15:54.621
1.8 million dollars.
Hammond, how much is yours?

15:54.621 --> 15:56.623
838 euros.

15:56.623 --> 15:59.492
- Thousand I'm guessing?
- Yes. It is thousands.

15:59.492 --> 16:02.362
Why has your car
got a number on the side?

16:02.362 --> 16:04.397
It's the Weissach edition,
this one.

16:04.397 --> 16:06.433
- You also get
titanium chassis bolts.
- Stupid.

16:06.433 --> 16:08.568
For just an extra £60,000.

16:08.568 --> 16:12.405
And a carbon-fiber
bonnet strut.

16:12.405 --> 16:13.806
Look at that.
How much does that save?

16:13.806 --> 16:17.244
- About 100 grams.
- Right there, 100 grams.

16:17.244 --> 16:19.779
Has the McLaren got
a carbon-fiber bonnet strut?

16:19.779 --> 16:23.150
- Doesn't need one.
- No, because my bonnet
doesn't go up

16:23.150 --> 16:25.552
because it will never
break down.

16:25.552 --> 16:28.488
And it's got silly doors.
Proper doors, silly doors.

16:28.488 --> 16:32.125
Mine does 34 miles
to the gallon.

16:32.125 --> 16:34.394
This does 94.

16:34.394 --> 16:36.529
- 94 miles to the gallon?
- 94mpg.

16:36.529 --> 16:38.731
Just remind me,
Porsche is owned by?

16:38.731 --> 16:40.667
That'll be Volkswagen.

16:46.106 --> 16:50.877
Soon the McLaren and
the Porsche were ready
for some shakedown laps.

16:50.877 --> 16:53.580
[REVVING]

16:53.580 --> 16:58.151
And for these we decided
we'd drive each other's cars.

17:02.489 --> 17:04.291
Straight away,
I can tell you

17:04.291 --> 17:07.760
that this doesn't have
the brutality or the savagery

17:07.760 --> 17:10.697
of the McLaren.

17:10.697 --> 17:14.734
Because it has rear-wheel
steering and four-wheel drive,

17:14.734 --> 17:17.637
it feels secure and safe.

17:17.637 --> 17:19.839
And that gives you
the confidence--

17:19.839 --> 17:22.309
[CHUCKLES]

17:22.309 --> 17:24.411
...to play about.

17:28.715 --> 17:30.617
